Bring bold Southwestern flavors to your table with these chicken and green pepper rice bowls. You'll serve a spiced mix of sautéed chicken, pepper, and onion over a bed of warm rice, then top it all off with Monterey Jack cheese and a charred corn salsa for a touch of smoky sweetness. All that's left to do? Finish with a drizzle of tangy crema!

== Rice ==

In a small #pot, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water, and a pinch of
@salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings, use 2 1/4 cups water.

== Charred Corn Salsa ==

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Drain @corn{1%unit}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Halve, core, and thinly slice
@long green pepper{1%unit} into strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@onion{1%unit}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan over high heat. Add corn and
cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and lightly charred in spots,
~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Cover pan if corn begins to pop!

Turn off heat; transfer corn to a small #bowl. Stir in @fresh red salsa{4%ounce};
set aside until ready to serve.

== Chicken and Veggies ==

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess
liquid.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for corn over medium-high
heat. Add chicken, green pepper, onion, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon},
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @cumin{1/2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until veggies are just beginning to soften,
~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Lower heat if chicken and veggies begin to brown too quickly.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp cumin.

> Save remaining cumin for another use.

Add 1/4 cup water and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring frequently, until
chicken is cooked through and sauce has slightly thickened,
~{2-3%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> For 4 servings, use 1/2 cup water and 2 TBSP butter.

== Crema ==

Place @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} in a second small #bowl. Add water 1 tsp at a
time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{} and top with chicken and veggies. Top with
@Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and corn salsa. Drizzle crema over everything and
serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.